{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1144,"text":"Across Europe and Central Asia,"},{"time":3870,"text":"approximately one million children live in large"},{"time":6430,"text":"residential institutions, usually known as orphanages."},{"time":10528,"text":"Most people imagine orphanages as a benign environment"},{"time":13586,"text":"that care for children."},{"time":15257,"text":"Others know more about the living conditions there,"},{"time":18488,"text":"but still think they're a necessary evil."},{"time":20940,"text":"After all, where else would we put all of those children"},{"time":24337,"text":"who don't have any parents?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":26488,"text":"But 60 years of research has demonstrated"},{"time":29955,"text":"that separating children from their families"},{"time":32211,"text":"and placing them in large institutions"},{"time":34563,"text":"seriously harms their health and development,"},{"time":37403,"text":"and this is particularly true for young babies."},{"time":40885,"text":"As we know, babies are born"},{"time":43029,"text":"without their full muscle development,"},{"time":45789,"text":"and that includes the brain."},{"time":47713,"text":"During the first three years of life, the brain grows"},{"time":50373,"text":"to its full size, with most of that growth taking place"},{"time":53143,"text":"in the first six months. The brain develops"},{"time":55763,"text":"in response to experience and to stimulation."},{"time":58989,"text":"Every time a young baby learns something new --"},{"time":62803,"text":"to focus its eyes,"},{"time":64330,"text":"to mimic a movement or a facial expression,"},{"time":67323,"text":"to pick something up, to form a word or to sit up --"},{"time":71313,"text":"new synaptic connections are being built in the brain."},{"time":74890,"text":"New parents are astonished by the rapidity of this learning."},{"time":78989,"text":"They are quite rightly amazed and delighted by their children's cleverness."},{"time":83897,"text":"They communicate their delight to their children,"},{"time":86481,"text":"who respond with smiles,"},{"time":88202,"text":"and a desire to achieve more and to learn more."},{"time":92604,"text":"This forming of the powerful attachment between child and parent"},{"time":96346,"text":"provides the building blocks for physical, social,"},{"time":99557,"text":"language, cognitive and psychomotor development."},{"time":103067,"text":"It is the model for all future relationships with friends,"},{"time":107281,"text":"with partners and with their own children."},{"time":110522,"text":"It happens so naturally in most families"},{"time":112938,"text":"that we don't even notice it. Most of us are unaware"},{"time":116042,"text":"of its importance to human development and, by extension,"},{"time":119472,"text":"to the development of a healthy society."},{"time":122371,"text":"And it's only when it goes wrong that we start to realize"},{"time":124913,"text":"the importance of families to children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127922,"text":"In August, 1993, I had my first opportunity to witness"},{"time":131858,"text":"on a massive scale the impact on children"},{"time":136016,"text":"of institutionalization and the absence of parenting."},{"time":140419,"text":"Those of us who remember the newspaper reports"},{"time":142856,"text":"that came out of Romania after the 1989 revolution"},{"time":146110,"text":"will recall the horrors of the conditions in some of those institutions."},{"time":150531,"text":"I was asked to help the director of a large institution to"},{"time":153290,"text":"help prevent the separation of children from their families."},{"time":157253,"text":"Housing 550 babies, this was Ceausescu's show orphanage,"},{"time":161438,"text":"and so I'd been told the conditions were much better."},{"time":164356,"text":"Having worked with lots of young children, I expected"},{"time":166806,"text":"the institution to be a riot of noise,"},{"time":169422,"text":"but it was as silent as a convent."},{"time":171285,"text":"It was hard to believe there were any children there at all,"},{"time":174731,"text":"yet the director showed me into room after room,"},{"time":177367,"text":"each containing row upon row of cots,"},{"time":180382,"text":"in each of which lay a child staring into space."},{"time":186398,"text":"In a room of 40 newborns, not one of them was crying."},{"time":190048,"text":"Yet I could see soiled nappies, and I could see"},{"time":192087,"text":"that some of the children were distressed,"},{"time":193659,"text":"but the only noise was a low, continuous moan."},{"time":197504,"text":"The head nurse told me proudly,"},{"time":199604,"text":"\"You see, our children are very well-behaved.\""},{"time":202825,"text":"Over the next few days, I began to realize"},{"time":205568,"text":"that this quietness was not exceptional."},{"time":207631,"text":"The newly admitted babies would cry for the first few hours,"},{"time":211404,"text":"but their demands were not met, and so eventually"},{"time":213393,"text":"they learned not to bother. Within a few days,"},{"time":216071,"text":"they were listless, lethargic, and staring into space"},{"time":219567,"text":"like all the others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221393,"text":"Over the years, many people and news reports"},{"time":224310,"text":"have blamed the personnel in the institutions"},{"time":226481,"text":"for the harm caused to the children, but often, one member"},{"time":229335,"text":"of staff is caring for 10, 20, and even 40 children."},{"time":233902,"text":"Hence they have no option but to implement a regimented program."},{"time":237964,"text":"The children must be woken at 7 and fed at 7:30."},{"time":241839,"text":"At 8, their nappies must be changed, so a staff member"},{"time":244351,"text":"may have only 30 minutes to feed 10 or 20 children."},{"time":247716,"text":"If a child soils its nappy at 8:30, he will have to wait"},{"time":251412,"text":"several hours before it can be changed again."},{"time":254371,"text":"The child's daily contact with another human being"},{"time":257020,"text":"is reduced to a few hurried minutes of feeding and changing,"},{"time":261488,"text":"and otherwise their only stimulation is the ceiling,"},{"time":264388,"text":"the walls or the bars of their cots."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268520,"text":"Since my first visit to Ceausescu's institution,"},{"time":271419,"text":"I've seen hundreds of such places across 18 countries,"},{"time":274552,"text":"from the Czech Republic to Sudan."},{"time":277344,"text":"Across all of these diverse lands and cultures,"},{"time":280328,"text":"the institutions, and the child's journey through them,"},{"time":283625,"text":"is depressingly similar."},{"time":286218,"text":"Lack of stimulation often leads to self-stimulating behaviors"},{"time":289328,"text":"like hand-flapping, rocking back and forth,"},{"time":292269,"text":"or aggression, and in some institutions, psychiatric drugs"},{"time":296080,"text":"are used to control the behavior of these children,"},{"time":298911,"text":"whilst in others, children are tied up to prevent them"},{"time":301112,"text":"from harming themselves or others."},{"time":304000,"text":"These children are quickly labeled as having disabilities"},{"time":306492,"text":"and transferred to another institution for children with disabilities."},{"time":309927,"text":"Most of these children will never leave the institution again."},{"time":314270,"text":"For those without disabilities, at age three,"},{"time":316933,"text":"they're transferred to another institution, and at age seven,"},{"time":319481,"text":"to yet another. Segregated according to age and gender,"},{"time":323434,"text":"they are arbitrarily separated from their siblings,"},{"time":325979,"text":"often without even a chance to say goodbye."},{"time":329867,"text":"There's rarely enough to eat. They are often hungry."},{"time":332645,"text":"The older children bully the little ones. They learn to"},{"time":335355,"text":"survive. They learn to defend themselves, or they go under."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338704,"text":"When they leave the institution, they find it really difficult"},{"time":342264,"text":"to cope and to integrate into society."},{"time":345559,"text":"In Moldova, young women raised in institutions"},{"time":348808,"text":"are 10 times more likely to be trafficked than their peers,"},{"time":352816,"text":"and a Russian study found that two years after leaving institutions,"},{"time":356972,"text":"young adults, 20 percent of them had a criminal record,"},{"time":361331,"text":"14 percent were involved in prostitution,"},{"time":364187,"text":"and 10 percent had taken their own lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368751,"text":"But why are there so many orphans in Europe"},{"time":371632,"text":"when there hasn't been a great deal of war or disaster in recent years?"},{"time":375503,"text":"In fact, more than 95 percent of these children have living parents,"},{"time":380087,"text":"and societies tend to blame these parents"},{"time":382076,"text":"for abandoning these children, but research shows that"},{"time":384839,"text":"most parents want their children, and that the primary drivers"},{"time":387960,"text":"behind institutionalization"},{"time":390279,"text":"are poverty, disability and ethnicity."},{"time":394476,"text":"Many countries have not developed inclusive schools,"},{"time":397575,"text":"and so even children with a very mild disability"},{"time":400279,"text":"are sent away to a residential special school,"},{"time":402855,"text":"at age six or seven."},{"time":404663,"text":"The institution may be hundreds of miles away from the family home."},{"time":408797,"text":"If the family's poor, they find it difficult to visit,"},{"time":411521,"text":"and gradually the relationship breaks down."},{"time":415639,"text":"Behind each of the million children in institutions,"},{"time":418942,"text":"there is usually a story of parents who are desperate"},{"time":422696,"text":"and feel they've run out of options, like Natalia in Moldova,"},{"time":427806,"text":"who only had enough money to feed her baby,"},{"time":430199,"text":"and so had to send her older son to the institution;"},{"time":433383,"text":"or Desi, in Bulgaria, who looked after her four children"},{"time":436423,"text":"at home until her husband died,"},{"time":439052,"text":"but then she had to go out to work full time,"},{"time":441295,"text":"and with no support, felt she had no option"},{"time":443442,"text":"but to place a child with disabilities in an institution;"},{"time":447274,"text":"or the countless young girls too terrified to tell their parents"},{"time":450428,"text":"they're pregnant, who leave their babies in a hospital;"},{"time":454014,"text":"or the new parents, the young couple who have"},{"time":456746,"text":"just found out that their firstborn child has a disability,"},{"time":461252,"text":"and instead of being provided with positive messages"},{"time":464307,"text":"about their child's potential, are told by the doctors,"},{"time":467154,"text":"\"Forget her, leave her in the institution,"},{"time":470210,"text":"go home and make a healthy one.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":473730,"text":"This state of affairs is neither necessary nor is it inevitable."},{"time":477262,"text":"Every child has the right to a family, deserves"},{"time":480389,"text":"and needs a family, and children are amazingly resilient."},{"time":484220,"text":"We find that if we get them out of institutions and into loving"},{"time":486902,"text":"families early on, they recover their developmental delays,"},{"time":490423,"text":"and go on to lead normal, happy lives."},{"time":493466,"text":"It's also much cheaper to provide support to families"},{"time":497027,"text":"than it is to provide institutions."},{"time":499546,"text":"One study suggests that a family support service"},{"time":502742,"text":"costs 10 percent of an institutional placement,"},{"time":505650,"text":"whilst good quality foster care"},{"time":507914,"text":"costs usually about 30 percent."},{"time":510906,"text":"If we spend less on these children but on the right services,"},{"time":513954,"text":"we can take the savings and reinvest them in high quality"},{"time":517906,"text":"residential care for those few children with extremely complex needs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522555,"text":"Across Europe, a movement is growing to shift the focus"},{"time":527092,"text":"and transfer the resources from large institutions"},{"time":529928,"text":"that provide poor quality care to community-based services"},{"time":533888,"text":"that protect children from harm and allow them to develop"},{"time":536613,"text":"to their full potential. When I first started to work in Romania"},{"time":540440,"text":"nearly 20 years ago, there were 200,000 children living"},{"time":544216,"text":"in institutions, and more entering every day."},{"time":547777,"text":"Now, there are less than 10,000, and"},{"time":550088,"text":"family support services are provided across the country."},{"time":553536,"text":"In Moldova, despite extreme poverty and the terrible effects"},{"time":557322,"text":"of the global financial crisis, the numbers of children"},{"time":560314,"text":"in institutions has reduced by more than 50 percent"},{"time":563098,"text":"in the last five years, and the resources are being"},{"time":566314,"text":"redistributed to family support services and inclusive schools."},{"time":570967,"text":"Many countries have developed national action plans for change."},{"time":574197,"text":"The European Commission and other major donors"},{"time":576718,"text":"are finding ways to divert money from institutions"},{"time":580198,"text":"towards family support, empowering communities"},{"time":583194,"text":"to look after their own children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585923,"text":"But there is still much to be done to end the systematic"},{"time":588726,"text":"institutionalization of children."},{"time":591094,"text":"Awareness-raising is required at every level of society."},{"time":594163,"text":"People need to know the harm that institutions cause to children,"},{"time":597687,"text":"and the better alternatives that exist."},{"time":600647,"text":"If we know people who are planning to support orphanages,"},{"time":603611,"text":"we should convince them to support family services instead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":607653,"text":"Together, this is the one form of child abuse"},{"time":610915,"text":"that we could eradicate in our lifetime."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613779,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":616371,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}